# Project Structure Guide

This is a cross-platform whiteboard application built with Rust and Slint. The codebase is organized into several key directories:

## Core Source Code
The main source code is in [src/](mdc:src) directory:
- [src/main.rs](mdc:src/main.rs) - Application entry point
- [src/app.rs](mdc:src/app.rs) - Core application logic
- [src/config.rs](mdc:src/config.rs) - Configuration management
- [src/error.rs](mdc:src/error.rs) - Error handling
- [src/storage.rs](mdc:src/storage.rs) - Data storage implementation
- [src/window.rs](mdc:src/window.rs) - Window management
- [src/ui/](mdc:src/ui) - UI components implementation

## UI Definition
The Slint UI definitions are stored in [ui/](mdc:ui) directory:
- [ui/main.slint](mdc:ui/main.slint) - Main window UI definition

## Documentation and Configuration
- [docs/](mdc:docs) - Project documentation
- [Cargo.toml](mdc:Cargo.toml) - Project dependencies and configuration